# In-situ core-glue equivalence (AGENT.md §6, README). Proves our whole core's glue (decode,
# the inline ALU, control, flags, the 13 state registers) ≡ RISC5.v with the 8 submodules
# black-boxed and assumed-equivalent (each proven separately). Driven by Yosys_equiv.run_proof.
# Placeholders (named WITHOUT braces here — substitution is blind): stubs = core_stubs.v (the
# port-only black-box module both sides reference); rtl = RISC5.v; ours/gate = our emitted
# gate (Core_blackbox.circuit); top = RISC5; renames = align our register names to RISC5.v's.
# equiv_make MERGES the matched black-box cells (checking their inputs via the $equiv on the
# named nets); cutpoint -blackbox then cuts the merged units' outputs to shared free signals
# (the assume side — sound on the leaf proofs), leaving pure glue that equiv_induct discharges.
read_verilog {stubs}
read_verilog {rtl}
read_verilog {ours}
hierarchy -check
proc
{renames}
opt
equiv_make {top} {gate} equiv
hierarchy -top equiv
cutpoint -blackbox
opt -full
equiv_simple
equiv_induct
equiv_status -assert
